  "105": "openspine-decision-log.md",
  "106": "D-051 — The agent-OS canon (AD-001..153) is decomposed into a dependency-edged change sequence; the stale later-changes placeholders are superseded or subsumed",
  "107": "OpenSpine",
  "108": "Gmail selected-thread email preview setup (Phase 2)",
  "109": "Telegram owner-control setup (Phase 1)",
  "110": "Tasks: Implement authority composition",
  "111": "Design: Digest-bound draft approval",
  "112": "Design: Gate action API",
  "113": "Tasks: Implement gate action API",
  "114": "Design: Selected-thread email preview slice",
  "115": "Design: Telegram owner control slice",
  "116": "Requirement: Selection tokens MUST be single-use, expiring, and scope-fixed",
  "117": "Authority growth",
  "118": "Kernel foundation",
  "119": "attrs",
  "120": "Design: Harden approval and budgets",
  "121": "Failure surfacing & operations",
  "122": "D-008 — Deterministic routing decides authority; agentic routing decides strategy",
  "123": "D-001 — Lyra is a runtime/substrate, not a single agent",
  "124": "D-039 — Draft-approval channel is a Telegram inline button (`callback_query`), not a text command",
  "125": "D-042 — Reply recipient is kernel-derived, never shell-supplied: newest non-owner sender, matched against a configured mailbox address",
  "126": "D-002 — First usable UX should include an owner control channel",
  "127": "D-003 — Gmail is a guarded workflow, not the whole product",
  "128": "D-004 — Every effectful action goes through `gate()`",
  "129": "D-005 — Private-data shell must be contained",
  "130": "D-009 — External content is data, not instruction",
  "131": "D-021 — Email domain is broader than Gmail",
  "132": "D-022 — Agent-owned inbox is distinct from owner mailbox access",
  "133": "D-023 — OpenSpine is the substrate; Lyra is a product built on it",
  "134": "D-024 — OpenSpec is the development/change-management layer, not the runtime",
  "135": "D-026 — Shell containment via a `SandboxDriver` trait (Process dev-only / Docker)",
  "136": "banner",
  "137": "ActionRequest",
  "138": "add_column_if_missing",
  "139": "Design: Backfill implemented capability specs",
  "140": "Design: Artifact lifecycle slice",
  "141": "Delegation & containment",
  "142": "Skills & workflows",
  "143": "Reflection & product surface",
  "144": "package.json",
  "145": "D-036 — Phase-2 thread selection is a kernel-recognized `/draft <thread_id>` command, not free-form NLU or a shell-supplied id",
  "146": "D-037 — Gmail OAuth via a plain refresh-token POST (no `oauth2` crate); `base64` promoted from transitive to direct dependency",
  "147": "D-038 — `resolve_owner_identity`'s `channel_trust` is caller-supplied, not hardcoded",
  "148": "D-040 — Pending (pre-approval) `ActionRequest`s are persisted in a new `action_requests` table",
  "149": "D-041 — `email.create_draft`'s digest composition: payload = `{subject, body}`, target = `{thread_id, connector, account_role, recipients}`",
  "150": "D-043 — `lyra.ui.preview` is extended (not duplicated) to propose the exact reviewed draft and attach the approval button",
  "151": "D-044 — Approved draft creation dispatches kernel-side; no new shell spawn",
  "152": "D-045 — WYSIWYS: a truncated preview refuses an approval button rather than splitting the message",
  "153": "D-046 — Grant budgets are enforced kernel-dispatch-side; the artifact budget counts only shell-initiated puts",
  "154": "D-047 — Task tokens are hashed at rest; expired grants are swept",
  "155": "D-048 — `artifact.activate` is the single canonical activation action id; every runtime proposal requires uniform owner approval; prompt templates are excluded from proposable kinds",
  "156": "D-049 — Capability specs are backfilled for subsystems implemented inside earlier slices",
  "157": "D-050 — `max_model_calls` is enforced with an atomic upsert, not a count-then-compare",
  "158": "D-006 — Identity is not authority",
  "159": "D-011 — Approval must be digest-bound",
  "160": "D-012 — Audit stores private payloads by encrypted/hash reference",
  "161": "D-013 — Dynamic behavior easy; dynamic authority hard",
  "162": "D-014 — Bootstrap/setup secrets bypass shell/model context",
  "163": "D-015 — Phase 1 should avoid final email send",
  "164": "D-016 — Capability packs are candidate profiles, not live authority",
  "165": "D-017 — Personas grant no authority",
  "166": "D-018 — Routes are declarative artifacts, not kernel code",
  "167": "D-020 — Railway/Docker/VPS are deployment targets, not core architecture",
  "168": "D-025 — Rust/Tokio substrate: storage, audit chain, and secrets handling",
  "169": "D-027 — Multi-provider model gateway with per-provider auth mode",
  "170": "D-028 — Canonical artifact format is YAML+serde; digests are `sha256:` over canonical JSON",
  "171": "D-029 — Gmail OAuth scopes: `readonly` + `compose`, send hard-denied at the gate",
  "172": "D-030 — Telegram carries the entire owner-control UX for phases 1–3",
  "173": "D-031 — Docker Compose is the first reference deployment target",
  "174": "D-032 — Kernel↔shell transport is HTTP/JSON with a per-task bearer token",
  "175": "D-033 — Action identifiers are exact-match dotted strings; unverified senders are audited and ignored",
  "176": "D-034 — `email.create_draft` is the one canonical action id; the qualified PRD §10.2 spelling is dropped",
  "177": "D-035 — Kernel advertises a separate `advertise_endpoint` from its `bind_addr`; no Unix-domain-socket transport for `ProcessDriver`",
  "178": "D-010 — Model calls with private context go through model gateway",
  "179": "D-019 — Implement minimal slice first, not full agent OS",
  "180": "why-openspine.md",
